{"title_page": "Pamilya Roces", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 Philippine television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| name = Pamilya Roces\n| image = Pamilya Roces title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card\n| show_name_2 = ''Family Jewels''<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmaworldwide.tv/programs/1/series/1/contemporary-drama/1/show/507/family-jewels/ |title=Family Jewels |accessdate=November 9, 2018}}</ref>\n| genre = [[Drama]]\n| creator = [[Denoy Navarro-Punio]]\n| writer = {{Plainlist|\n* Denoy Navarro-Punio\n* Kenneth De Leon\n* Evie Macapugay\n* Renei Dimla}}\n| director = [[Joel Lamangan]]\n| creative_director = [[Roy Iglesias|Roy C. Iglesias]]\n| starring = {{plainlist|\n* [[Carla Abellana]]\n* [[Gabbi Garcia]]\n* [[Sophie Albert]]\n* [[Shaira Diaz]]\n* [[Jasmine Curtis-Smith]]}}\n| theme_music_composer = Ann Figueroa\n| opentheme = \"Tao Lang\" by [[Maricris Garcia]]\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| num_episodes = 50\n| list_episodes = List of Pamilya Roces episodes\n| executive_producer = Darling Pulido-Torres\n| location = Philippines\n| editor = {{Plainlist|\n* Robert Ryan Reyes\n* Ver Custodio}}\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| runtime = 37-41 minutes\n| company = GMA Entertainment Group \n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired = {{start date|2018|10|8}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|2018|12|14}}\n| website = http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/pamilya_roces\n}}\n\n'''''Pamilya Roces''''' (International title: ''Family Jewels'' / {{translation|Roces Family}}) is a 2018 [[Philippine television drama]] series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. Directed by [[Joel Lamangan]], it stars [[Carla Abellana]], [[Gabbi Garcia]], [[Sophie Albert]], [[Shaira Diaz]] and [[Jasmine Curtis-Smith]]. It premiered on October 8, 2018, replacing ''[[Inday Will Always Love You]]'' on the network's Telebabad line up. The series concluded on December 14, 2018 with a total of 50 episodes. It was replaced by ''[[My Golden Life]]'' in its timeslot.\n\n==Premise==\nRoces family have wealth and power. They are the owners of the biggest jewelry business in the country. While the patriarch has three families and when he suffers from a heart attack, his families rush to his side. The lives of three women and five sisters get complicated as their lives intertwined.<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/pamilya_roces/about/ |title=Pamilya Roces |accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Carla Abellana, 2014 (cropped).jpg \n|caption1 = Carla Abellana portrays Crystal Rose Austria Roces-Javellana.\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Gabbi Garcia (2) - cropped.jpg\n|caption2 = Gabbi Garcia portrays Jade Austria Roces. \n|width2 = 150\n|image3 = Gloria Diaz Miss Universe 2016.jpg\n|caption3 = Gloria Diaz portrays Natalia Austria\u2013Roces.\n|width3 = 150\n|image4 = Christian Bautista.jpg\n|caption4 = Christian Bautista portrays Ralph Gomez. \n|width4 = 150\n}}\n\n<!--Official cast billing from GMA Network-->\n;Lead cast\n* [[Carla Abellana]] as Crystal Rose Austria Roces-Javellana<ref name=\"July\"/><ref name=\"Debut\">{{cite web |title='Pamilya Roces' makes \"nakakalokang\" debut on GMA Telebabad |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/pamilya_roces/44474/pamilya-roces-makes-nakakalokang-debut-on-gma-telebabad/story |website=GMANetwork.com |accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Gabbi Garcia]] as Jade Austria Roces<ref name=\"July\">{{cite web|URL=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/showbiznews/news/41923/just-in-jasmine-curtis-smith-overwhelmed-sa-kanyang-unang-soap-sa-kapuso-network/story |title=Jasmine Curtis Smith, overwhelmed sa kanyang unang soap sa Kapuso network |date=July 11, 2018 |accessdate=July 12, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Sophie Albert]] as Amber Bolocboc Roces-Gomez<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Shaira Diaz]]  as Amethyst \"Amy\" Renacia Roces<ref name=\"July\"/>\n* [[Jasmine Curtis-Smith]] as Pearl Renacia Quirante<ref name=\"July\"/>\n\n;Supporting cast\n* [[Roi Vinzon]] as Rodolfo \"Rod\" Gardamonte Roces<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Gloria Diaz]] as Natalia Austria-Roces<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Snooky Serna]] as Camilla Vera-Austria<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Elizabeth Oropesa]] as Violeta \"Violet/Violy\" Bolocboc<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Rocco Nacino]] as Hugoberto \"Hugo\" Ponciano Javellana<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Andr\u00e9 Paras]] as Gareth Austria<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Christian Bautista]] as Ralph Gomez<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Mika Dela Cruz]] as Donnatella \"Donna\" Rosales<ref>{{cite web|author=Gonzales, Rommel |title=Former TV5 star Shaira Diaz feels fortunate to join this new Kapuso show |url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/28577/former-tv5-star-shaira-diaz-feels-fortunate-to-join-this-new-kapuso-show |website=PEP.ph |accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref>\n* Manolo Pedrosa as Hilario \"Gil\" Figueroa<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n\n;Guest cast\n* [[Ana Roces]] as Lily Renacia<ref name=\"Debut\"/>\n* [[Jim Pebanco]] as Val\n* [[Arianne Bautista]] as Kate\n* [[Mike Tan]] as young Rodolfo\n* Julia Lee as Stella\n* Tony Mabesa as Manolo\n* Jules Dela Paz as Yves\n* Angel Guardian as Zara\n* Jana Trias as Betsy\n* Renerich Ocon as Elvie\n* [[Frances Makil-Ignacio]] as Marilou \"Lulu\" Lucero\n* Allysa del Real as Tiffany / Tiff\n* Michael Angelo Lobrin as Winston Go\n* Leonora Ca\u00f1o as Diane\n* Nicole Donesa as Bebe\n* Kristof Garcia as Tristan\n* Jon Romano as Lando Macaraeg\n* Karlo Duterte as Gordon\n* [[Ashley Ortega]] as Corinne\n* [[Katrina Halili]] as Maria Eloisa \"Maisa\" Renacia Quirante / Maisa Sampaguita<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=1993535124076839&id=161255523971484 |title=Abangan si Katrina Halili bilang Maria Eloisa sa Pamilya Roces |accessdate=November 25, 2018}}</ref>\n* William Lorenzo as Virgil Quirante / Vermont\n* Emilio Garcia as Rajo Brillantes III\n\n==Production==\n[[Teresita Marquez]] was cast to play a supporting role, but later back out during pre-production due to the show's sensitive scenes. [[Sophie Albert]] took her role.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/pepalerts/pep-troika/22766/winwyn-marquez-nag-back-out-sa-pamilya-roces-dahil-sa-sensitive-scenes |title=Winwyn Marquez, nag-back out sa Pamilya Roces dahil sa sensitive\u2026 |date=August 24, 2018 |accessdate=August 24, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Ratings==\nAccording to [[AGB Nielsen Philippines]]' Nationwide Urban Television Audience Measurement People in television homes, the pilot episode of ''Pamilya Roces'' earned a 7.4% rating.<ref>{{cite web|title=Alden Richards, aminadong hirap ang Victor Magtanggol sa Ang Probinsyano |author=PEP Troika |date=October 11, 2018 |url=https://www.pep.ph/pepalerts/pep-troika/23445/alden-richards-aminadong-hirap-ang-victor-magtanggol-sa-ang-probinsyano |accessdate=October 17, 2018}}</ref> While the final episode scored a 9.9% rating.<ref>{{Cite web \n|url=https://twitter.com/for__keeps/status/1074642185323085825? |title=Rommel Villegas on Twitter: \"#PamilyaRoces finale episode outscores its rival program based on AGB Nielsen TV Ratings for Friday, December 14, 2018.\" |date=December 17, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2019}}</ref> The series had its highest rating on November 22, 2018 with a 9.4% rating.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GoodThing193/status/1065897125970567168? |title=Yera Calma on Twitter: \"AGB Nielsen NUTAM People ratings November 22, 2018\" |date=November 23, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official site|http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/pamilya_roces}}\n* {{IMDB title|9083168}}\n\n[[Category:GMA Network drama series]]\n[[Category:Philippine drama television series]]\n[[Category:Comedy-drama television series]]\n[[Category:2018 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2018 Philippine television series endings]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-prog-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 Philippine television series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Pamilya Roces\n| image = Pamilya Roces title card.jpg\n| caption = Title card\n| show_name_2 = Family Jewels<ref>{{cite web|URL=http://www.gmaworldwide.tv/programs/1/series/1/contemporary-drama/1/show/507/family-jewels/ |title=Family Jewels |accessdate=November 9, 2018}}</ref>\n| genre = [[Drama]]\n| creator = [[Denoy Navarro-Punio]]\n| writer = {{Plainlist|\n* Denoy Navarro-Punio\n* Kenneth De Leon\n* Evie Macapugay\n* Renei Dimla}}\n| director = [[Joel Lamangan]]\n| creative_director = [[Roy Iglesias|Roy C. Iglesias]]\n| starring = {{plainlist|\n* [[Carla Abellana]]\n* [[Gabbi Garcia]]\n* [[Sophie Albert]]\n* [[Shaira Diaz]]\n* [[Jasmine Curtis-Smith]]}}\n| theme_music_composer = Ann Figueroa\n| opentheme = \"Tao Lang\" by [[Maricris Garcia]]\n| country = [[Philippines]]\n| language = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]]\n| num_episodes = 50\n| list_episodes = List of Pamilya Roces episodes\n| executive_producer = Darling Pulido-Torres\n| location = Philippines\n| editor = {{Plainlist|\n* Robert Ryan Reyes\n* Ver Custodio}}\n| camera = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| runtime = 37-41 minutes\n| company = GMA Entertainment Group \n| network = [[GMA Network]]\n| picture_format = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired = {{start date|2018|10|8}}\n| last_aired = {{end date|2018|12|14}}\n| website = http://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/pamilya_roces\n}}\n\n'''''Pamilya Roces''''' (International title: ''Family Jewels'' / {{translation|Roces Family}}) is a 2018 [[Philippine television drama]] series broadcast by [[GMA Network]]. Directed by [[Joel Lamangan]], it stars [[Carla Abellana]], [[Gabbi Garcia]], [[Sophie Albert]], [[Shaira Diaz]] and [[Jasmine Curtis-Smith]]. It premiered on October 8, 2018, replacing ''[[Inday Will Always Love You]]'' on the network's Telebabad line up. The series concluded on December 14, 2018 with a total of 50 episodes. It was replaced by ''[[My Golden Life]]'' in its timeslot.\n\n==Premise==\nRoces family have wealth and power. They are the owners of the biggest jewelry business in the country. While the patriarch has three families and when he suffers from a heart attack, his families rush to his side. The lives of three women and five sisters get complicated as their lives intertwined.<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/pamilya_roces/about/ |title=Pamilya Roces |accessdate=October 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Carla Abellana, 2014 (cropped).jpg \n|caption1 = Carla Abellana portrays Crystal Rose Austria Roces-Javellana.\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Gabbi Garcia (2) - cropped.jpg\n|caption2 = Gabbi Garcia portrays Jade Austria Roces. \n|width2 = 150\n|image3 = Gloria Diaz Miss Universe 2016.jpg\n|caption3 = Gloria Diaz portrays Natalia Austria\u2013Roces.\n|width3 = 150\n|image4 = Christian Bautista.jpg\n|caption4 = Christian Bautista portrays Ralph Gomez. \n|width4 = 150\n}}\n\n<!--Official cast billing from GMA Network-->\n;Lead cast\n* [[Carla Abellana]] as Crystal Rose Austria Roces-Javellana<ref name=\"July\"/><ref name=\"Debut\">{{cite web |title='Pamilya Roces' makes \"nakakalokang\" debut on GMA Telebabad |url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/tv/pamilya_roces/44474/pamilya-roces-makes-nakakalokang-debut-on-gma-telebabad/story |website=GMANetwork.com |accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Gabbi Garcia]] as Jade Austria Roces<ref name=\"July\">{{cite web|URL=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/showbiznews/news/41923/just-in-jasmine-curtis-smith-overwhelmed-sa-kanyang-unang-soap-sa-kapuso-network/story |title=Jasmine Curtis Smith, overwhelmed sa kanyang unang 